# 1. 次なる仕事は

Airi: Nice work, everyone! Our meeting for that show went pretty well. It's really going to be our first time appearing as regulars.
Minori: Yeah! But I was sooo nervous the whole time!
Haruka: You're always nervous, but today was on a different level. You were as stiff as a robot before we'd even entered the building...
Airi: The gate at the entrance even closed on you. But I guess it is like you to mix up your entry ID with your commuter pass...
Shizuku: Still, I'm glad that you were able to get in after realizing what you'd done.
Minori: I-I'm so sorry about what happened back there!
Saito: Hehe. I know you were nervous, but I'm really glad that our meeting went as well as it did...
Airi: Yeah, everything went perfectly! And it was so easy to talk about stuff since we'd worked with the director before on a different show.
Shizuku: The producer we got to meet for the first time also seemed like a very nice person.
Haruka: Yeah. They even took the time to ask us all about what kind of message we were hoping to send.
Haruka: I know this was just a chance for us to meet everyone, but I'm really looking forward to how things are going to turn out.
Saito: Me too. I have a feeling that you're all going to do really well on this program!
Saito: Oh, I just remembered. There's another matter that I'd like to discuss with all of you.
Shizuku: Another matter?
Saito: Yes. So, I received an offer regarding a live stage performance.
Shizuku: A live stage performance...?!
Saito: Yes, for an outdoor music event called the “Idol Lovers Festival.” You may or may not have—
Airi & Minori: Idol Lovers?!
Saito: Ah, so you are familiar with it.
Haruka: I have to think that every idol would be.
Shizuku: Yes, and not just idols. Fans of idols as well. It's famous for being like a rite of passage for young idol groups.
Saito: Right. And those who do well at this festival tend to become very successful.
Saito: The media, music producers, agency scouts and countless others from the industry are usually present. As a result, this event has become a very big deal.
Airi: Still, this is Idol Lovers we're talking about. You can't just sign up and perform there.
Airi: You usually need a certain amount of experience and name recognition in order to receive an invite...
Saito: Yes, and this offer is no exception. In other words...
Saito: They've decided to invite MORE MORE JUMP! because you've all been able to build up a good track record.
Airi: Wait, we have...?
Minori: Th-This is incredible...! We've really been invited to perform at Idol Lovers...?!
Shizuku: So, does this mean the festival's operators have been watching what we've been doing...?
Haruka: The channel it airs on requires a subscription, but it is aired live on TV every year.
Haruka: They even make it available online for a few weeks afterward.
Haruka: This festival is a great chance for us to reach even more new people.
Minori: Yeah!
Minori: Also, it'd be really hard to put on shows right now because of scheduling and budgeting issues.
Minori: But if we're being invited to perform at Idol Lovers, then we don't have to worry about any of those things.
Shizuku: Our fans are going to be so excited! A lot of them have been commenting on our streams about how much they want another show!
Haruka: True. When you put it that way, there's no reason for us to not accept.
Haruka: What do you think, Airi?
Airi: Oh...
Minori: Airi?
Airi: Oh... Sorry, I didn't mean to space out.
Airi: The truth is, I've been wanting to perform at Idol Lovers since when I was still with QT...
Airi: Which is why I'm sorta having a hard time believing that we've been invited.
Haruka: Then, I think we have our answer.
Airi: Yup...
Airi: We're gonna go on that stage and give it absolutely everything we've got!
Saito: In that case, I'll let them know that you accept their invitation!
Haruka: Okay, thank you.
Minori: Then, we gotta start working on our set list and dances for it today!
Saito: Oh, sorry. There's actually one more thing I need to mention...
Shizuku: One more thing?
Saito: Yes, it has to do with the festival's special ensemble.
Minori: Oh, the thing they do every year! You always get to see different groups perform and interact with one another!
Saito: Yes, this has apparently involved everything from dance battles to eating competitions.
Saito: But this year, they'll be pairing up two different groups to do a joint performance.
Haruka: A joint performance...?
Minori: Wait, does that mean we get to perform with another group?!
Shizuku: W-What kind of group will we be paired with...?
Saito: Nothing has been set in stone yet, but the name that's been brought up is...
Saito: A group called “ReLight”.
Airi: ReLight...? Aren't they...?
Haruka: The group that has Mr. Hiiragi as their producer. The same person that helped build ASRUN.
Minori: They've been appearing on TV and in magazines a ton lately!
Minori: I've watched them a few times on TV too. They're really amazing singers and their dancing is impeccable...
Minori: I can't help but keep thinking about how did they learn to dance like that!
Shizuku: I've been hearing their name more often recently, but I didn't realize they were that good!
Shizuku: And to think that we may get to perform with them on stage? This is so exciting, and such an honor.
Saito: Yes, it is... In terms of popularity, you really can't ask for more...
Haruka: Is something concerning you?
Saito: Oh, not concerning per se...
Saito: But despite ReLight's popularity, they've been receiving a lot of nasty comments on social media.
Airi: Oh...
Airi: Come to think of it, I've also noticed that...
Airi: I remember one person saying, “They aren't good. They just have a big agency backing them.” Another even said, “They're all rotten on the inside.”
Minori: Wh-Wh-Wh-What?! They've never given off that impression on TV or in any magazine interview.
Minori: I can't really say what their personalities are like, but I totally get why they're so popular right now! I mean, they really are amazing at singing and dancing!
Saito: Right. Those are all just rumors anyway, so it's nothing to dwell on...
Saito: But since there's a chance that you'll be performing alongside them, I thought it'd be good to at least be aware of this sort of thing.
Shizuku: Saito...
Airi: We appreciate you being so careful and attentive, but I'm sure we'll be fine.
Haruka: I agree. Because our goal remains unchanged.
Minori: Right! We're gonna go to Idol Lovers and give everyone the best performance we possibly can!
Saito: You're all absolutely right! I apologize for being so paranoid!
Saito: It is true that ReLight has been putting on incredible performances, so I'm sure this festival should end up being a good learning experience for all of you.
Airi: (A good learning experience...)
Saito: So, please do your best! I promise to give you all the support I can!
Minori: Thank you very much!
Airi: (Yeah, when it comes to idols, ReLight has recently started standing head and shoulders above the rest...)
Airi: (And being asked to perform with them means that the spotlight's going to be on our abilities...)
Airi: As a singer, as a dancer and as a variety show star! I'm gonna keep evolving and become a super idol who can do it all!
Airi: (This might be my chance to make what I said back then come true.)
Airi: (In order to make our joint performance with them a success...)
Airi: (And to put on the perfect show, I have to do my absolute best!)
